<item>
            <title>[LU-12716] text file busy errors - Lustre 2.10.7 clients, 2.10.4 servers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12716</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have increasing occurrences of &quot;text file busy&quot; errors when trying to execute either scripts or binaries that are on our Lustre filesystem. This is blocking productivity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The only work-around we know of is to copy the file to a new file, then it (sometimes) works. This seems to happen at random, to random scripts and binaries.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="56803">LU-12716</key>
            <summary>text file busy errors - Lustre 2.10.7 clients, 2.10.4 servers</summary>
