                <updated>Fri, 11 Oct 2019 18:07:21 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Fri, 11 Oct 2019 18:07:21 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>Lustre 2.10.7</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="256248" author="jerwin" created="Fri, 11 Oct 2019 17:25:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peter, I do not see an option to close this bug, can you please do it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="256247" author="jerwin" created="Fri, 11 Oct 2019 17:24:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was narrowed down to the scenario where files are copied/created on the Lustre file system through an NFS mount.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Lustre/OPA network) , NFS server &amp;lt;--&amp;gt; non-Lustre node&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the non-Lustre node created a file on the Lustre file system through an NFS mount, subsequent accesses to that file from other nodes showed the Test file busy error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also upgraded all Lustre to 2.12.2 and will re-open if this becomes a blocker again. For now we have a workaround, that is to not use the NFS share to create files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="253879" author="pjones" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2019 22:23:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that this might be dealt with if you move to a more current release on your servers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
